--Nigeria is to join the league of deep offshore oil producers in the world when the nation's first deep water oil field commences production in the year 2003.
the "Bonga" oil field is located 120 kilometers off the coast of the oil-producing Niger Delta region in water more than 1,000 meters deep.
The country is now executing an oil project through Shell Nigeria Exploration and Production Company (SNEPCO) at a cost of 2.7 billion U.S. dollars.
Shell's deep water oil exploration in its Bonga field has come up with exciting results which can be compared to the huge discoveries made
